      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the dreaded drip-drip-drip of a bathroom sink, a sound that even the most seasoned goblin would find unbearable. To tackle this pesky problem, you'll need a few tools, much like a goblin would need a sturdy pickaxe and a trusty lantern to navigate the dark caves. First, grab a pair of pliers or a wrench to loosen the handle, then a screwdriver to remove the old washer. Once you've got that out, you'll need a new washer, which you can find at your local hardware store, much like a goblin would scour the forest for shiny trinkets. After you've replaced the washer, tighten the handle back up and test your handiwork. If the drip-drip-drip persists, you might need to call in a professional, much like a goblin would seek out a wizard for help. Good luck, brave adventurer!",
